{"id":"2207.05639","submitter":"Anastasia Halfpap","authors":"Anastasia Halfpap, Nathan Lemons, and Cory Palmer","title":"Positive co-degree density of hypergraphs","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The minimum positive co-degree of a non-empty $r$-graph ${H}$, denoted\n$\\delta_{r-1}^+( {H})$, is the maximum $k$ such that if $S$ is an $(r-1)$-set\ncontained in a hyperedge of $ {H}$, then $S$ is contained in at least $k$\ndistinct hyperedges of $ {H}$. Given a family ${F}$ of $r$-graphs, we introduce\nthe {\\it positive co-degree Tur\\'an number} $\\mathrm{co^+ex}(n, {F})$ as the\nmaximum positive co-degree $\\delta_{r-1}^+(H)$ over all $n$-vertex $r$-graphs\n$H$ that do not contain $F$ as a subhypergraph.\n  In this paper we concentrate on the behavior of $\\mathrm{co^+ex}(n, {F})$ for\n$3$-graphs $F$. In particular, we determine asymptotics and bounds for several\nwell-known concrete $3$-graphs $F$ (e.g.\\ $K_4^-$ and the Fano plane).\n  We also show that, for $3$-graphs, the limit \\[ \\gamma^+(F) := \\limsup_{n\n\\rightarrow \\infty} \\frac{\\mathrm{co^+ex}(n, {F})}{n} \\] ``jumps'' from $0$ to\n$1/3$, i.e., it never takes on values in the interval $(0,1/3)$, and we\ncharacterize which $3$-graphs $F$ have $\\gamma^+(F)=0$. Our motivation comes\nprimarily from the study of (ordinary) co-degree Tur\\'an numbers where a number\nof results have been proved that inspire our results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jul 2022 16:13:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-13"}
