ures,\npotential deviations from the CP include variations of cosmological parameters\non the sky, discrepancies in the cosmic dipoles, and mysterious alignments in\nquasar polarizations and galaxy spins. While it is possible that a host of\nobservational systematics are impacting results, it is equally plausible that\nprecision cosmology may have outgrown the FLRW paradigm, an extremely pragmatic\nbut non-fundamental symmetry assumption.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jul 2022 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 22 Aug 2022 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 13 Oct 2022 12:01:44 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2023 19:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-02"}
