 $r_{\\rm mass}- M_*$ relation and we\nfind that it has a shallower slope and shows less redshift evolution than the\n$r_{\\rm light} - M_*$ relation. This applies both to star-forming and quiescent\ngalaxies. We discuss some of the implications of using $r_{\\rm mass}$ instead\nof $r_{\\rm light}$, including an investigation of the size-inclination bias and\na comparison to numerical simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2022 00:05:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-29"}
