ible for the accretion of gaseous C and O. Depending on the\nplanet's migration history order-of-magnitude differences in atmospheric C/H\nand O/H are expected. Our simulations also predict super-solar N/H for $\\tau$\nBo\\\"otis b and solar N/H for WASP-77A b. We conclude that pebble evaporation is\na key ingredient to explain the variety of exoplanet atmospheres, because it\ncan explain both, sub- and super-solar atmospheric abundances.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2022 09:34:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 Jul 2022 09:41:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-21"}
